# MixAuto Android Car Launcher

Custom HOME launcher for Eonon head units. Jetpack Compose + Material 3, sensor orientation (portrait + landscape), automotive-grade dark UI.

## Stack

- Package: `com.kyuusanq3.mixauto`
- Compose BOM `2024.06.00`, Kotlin `1.9.24`, Compose Compiler `1.5.14`
- Entry: `MainActivity` → `MixAutoTheme` → `DashboardScreen`
- See `AGENTS.md` at repo root for full layout and build instructions

## UI rules

- Use `MixAutoTheme`; never light mode — head unit is always dark
- Colors: `OledBlack`, `DeepCharcoal`, `DarkSurface`, `ElectricCyan` from `ui/theme/Color.kt`
- Sizes: `CarDimensions` object — min tap target 64dp, primary 84dp
- Text: prefer `CarHeadlineText`, `CarBodyText`, `CarLabelText` from `ui/theme/Type.kt` (ellipsis + maxLines enforced)
- Import theme text composables explicitly when used in dashboard files

## Layout structure

- `DashboardScreen.kt`: portrait Column (map → media → horizontal dock) or landscape Row/Column; map via `CarMapViewContainer` | media + shortcuts; `mapMediaRatio` slider in settings (default 0.6)
- Map: `CarMapEngine` interface in `domain/map/`; swap `MapLibreEngineImpl()` in `MainActivity` only
- `CarMapViewContainer.kt`: `AndroidView` + lifecycle forwarding + HUD + search overlay trigger
- `ShortcutDock.kt`: dock toggles App Drawer / Music / **Voice Search (mic)** / Map Data / Launcher Settings; `ActivePanel.APP_DRAWER` opens `AppDrawerOverlay` over map+media only (shortcut bar stays visible)

## Map engine architecture

```
MainActivity (mapEngine = MapLibreEngineImpl())
  └── DashboardScreen(mapEngine)
        └── CarMapViewContainer(engine)
              ├── AndroidView → MapLibreEngineImpl.createMapView()
              ├── HUD from engine.uiState.collectAsState()
              └── NavigationSearchOverlay → searchDestination() / navigateToCoordinates()
```

- Style: inline OSM raster JSON (`tile.openstreetmap.org`) — not `demotiles.maplibre.org` (no PH coverage)
- Routing: `routing.openstreetmap.de/routed-car` OSRM API (not `router.project-osrm.org` — returns 403); `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0` required; route line via GeoJsonSource + LineLayer `#00CBD6`
- Search: Nominatim with `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0`
- Location: `MapLibreFusedLocationEngineImpl` (AOSP, no Google Services dep); runtime `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION` + `ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION` both requested
- No `play-services-location` dependency — app must work on Eonon/AOSP devices without Google Play Services

## Shortcut packages (Eonon / AOSP)

- Settings: `com.android.settings`
- Radio: try `com.android.fmradio`, `com.caf.fmradio`, `com.eonon.radio`
- Bluetooth: settings package or `Settings.ACTION_BLUETOOTH_SETTINGS` fallback

## Manifest

- HOME + DEFAULT + LAUNCHER intent-filters on `MainActivity`
- `launchMode="singleTask"`, `screenOrientation="sensor"`

## Build (Windows CLI)

Set `JAVA_HOME` to Android Studio `jbr` before `.\gradlew.bat assembleDebug`.

## Lessons learned

- Missing import for `CarLabelText` in `DashboardScreen.kt` caused compile failure — always import all `Car*Text` composables used in a file
- Kotlin and Compose Compiler versions must stay paired in `gradle/libs.versions.toml`
- Removed `activity_main.xml`; dashboard is 100% Compose — do not recreate XML main layout
- Gradle in Cursor terminal may fail without `JAVA_HOME`; Android Studio build works with embedded JDK
- MapView lifecycle race: `DisposableEffect` calls `onStart`/`onResume` before `AndroidView` factory runs — call `view.onStart()`/`view.onResume()` in `createMapView()` after `onCreate(null)`
- MapLibre 11.x removed `LocationEngineProvider` — use `LocationEngineProxy(AndroidLocationEngineImpl(ctx))` for emulator compatibility
- `demotiles.maplibre.org` has limited regional coverage; use OSM raster tiles for Philippines/global
- Map loads before location permission dialog — `MainActivity` must call `retryLocationActivation()` when permission already granted, not only after dialog
- Emulator mock GPS: `getLastKnownLocation` often null until `requestLocationUpdates(GPS_PROVIDER, …)` fires; refresh on `onResume` after Extended Controls changes
- `CarMapViewContainer` needs `lifecycle-runtime-compose` for `LocalLifecycleOwner`
- After OSRM route draw, `showRouteThenDive()` shows a 2 s `LatLngBounds` overview then dives to `CameraMode.TRACKING_GPS` (zoom 17.5, tilt 55°) — do not set `TRACKING` immediately after route draw or it snaps back before the dive
- `ShortcutDock` lazy list keys must use stable item keys (`music_player`, `voice_search`, `map_data`, `app_drawer`, `launcher_settings`); wrap horizontal/vertical branches in `key(isHorizontal, isLeftHandDrive)` — toggling layout or LHD changes icon order and can crash with duplicate keys
- Cached `MapView` in `MapLibreEngineImpl.createMapView()`: detach from parent via `(parent as? ViewGroup)?.removeView()` before returning to a new `AndroidView`
- Do not call `engine.onDestroy()` in `CarMapViewContainer` composable `onDispose` — only forward `ON_DESTROY` from activity lifecycle; layout changes remove/re-add the composable but must keep the map engine alive
- Emulator GPS (`adb emu geo fix`, Extended Controls) delivers 0 location reports on some AVDs — this is an AVD-level failure, not an app bug; test location on a physical device
- `MapLibreEngineImpl` registers GPS location listener ONCE via `listenersRegistered` flag — do not tear down and re-register on every `onResume`; rapid re-registration causes AppOps `op=GPS: Operation not started` errors and no fixes are delivered
- `forceLocationUpdate(location)` on `locationComponent` is required to push fixes into MapLibre's blue dot; store fix in `pendingLocationFix` if component not yet activated, flush in `activateLocationTracking()`
- `navigateToCoordinates()` falls back to map camera center (`resolveMapViewOrigin()`) when GPS is null and camera zoom ≥ 10 — allows routing on emulator without GPS fix
- Do NOT add `play-services-location` or any `com.google.android.gms` dependency — app targets AOSP head units with no Google Services
- `router.project-osrm.org` returns 403 for third-party apps — use `routing.openstreetmap.de/routed-car` in `fetchOsrmRoute()`; set `User-Agent: MixAutoCarLauncher/1.0` on OSRM requests (same as Nominatim)
- Turn-by-turn navigation: `fullRouteSteps` / `currentStepIndex` in `MapLibreEngineImpl`; `evaluateStepAdvancement()` runs on GPS fixes when `isNavigating` — do not overwrite `streetName` with "Current location" during navigation
- Step advance threshold 25 m; arrival at 15 m from destination or when step index exhausts; `navigationArrivalTriggered` prevents duplicate arrival coroutines
- `startFreeDrive()` removes route layer/source, resets `MapUiState`, snaps once via `snapCameraToGpsIfNeeded()` — do not re-snap on every GPS fix (causes camera twitching)
- Free drive camera: `FREE_DRIVE_ZOOM` 17.5 / `FREE_DRIVE_TILT` 50° / `CameraMode.TRACKING_GPS`; full nav uses zoom 18.5 / tilt 58°
- One-time snap: `hasSnappedCameraToGps` gates `snapCameraToGpsIfNeeded()`; use `moveCamera` then `TRACKING_GPS` — do not loop animated `setCameraMode` or stale-target checks on GPS updates
- Style-load callback calls `startFreeDrive()` after `activateLocationTracking()`; `retryLocationActivation()` must NOT call `startFreeDrive()` again (duplicate snap/twitch)
- Enabling `CameraMode.TRACKING` at wide fallback zoom (6) locks the visual view zoomed out even when `cameraPosition.zoom` reports 14–16 — snap after location component is active
- End navigation button in `CarMapViewContainer` (Close icon, red tint) calls `engine.startFreeDrive()` when `isNavigating`
- 3D nav camera: `showRouteThenDive()` sets `CameraMode.NONE` + `cancelTransitions()`, animates bounds in `ROUTE_OVERVIEW_ANIMATION_MS` (2 s), holds full-route view for `ROUTE_OVERVIEW_HOLD_MS` (10 s) with `routeOverviewProgress` timer bar in `CarMapViewContainer`; then `enterNavigationCamera()` — guard with `_uiState.value.isNavigating`; cancel `routeOverviewJob` in `startFreeDrive()`
- Nav dive camera: `enterNavigationCamera()` must NOT call `zoomWhileTracking`/`tiltWhileTracking` right after `TRACKING_GPS` — MapLibre ignores them while camera mode is transitioning; use `CameraMode.NONE` → `map.animateCamera(zoom 18.5 / tilt 58°)` → set `TRACKING_GPS` in `CancelableCallback.onFinish` (same snap pattern as free drive)
- Use `RenderMode.GPS` (not `COMPASS`) for heading-up driving view; set on `activateLocationTracking()` and before nav/free-drive camera modes
- Manual pan/zoom sets `isCameraDetached` via `MapLibreMap.OnCameraMoveStartedListener.REASON_API_GESTURE`; recenter button in `CarMapViewContainer` calls `engine.recenterCamera()`
- `MainActivity` uses `WindowCompat.setDecorFitsSystemWindows(window, false)` + `WindowInsetsControllerCompat.show(systemBars())` — root `DashboardScreen` must apply `systemBarsPadding()` so content sits below status/nav bars; head units with zero insets get no extra padding
- Do **not** set `android:windowFullscreen` in `themes.xml` — it hides the system status/notification bar on Eonon head units; keep `windowContentOverlay` @null only
- Portrait: map `weight(mapMediaRatio)`, media `weight(1 - ratio)`, horizontal `ShortcutDock` at bottom with wrap-content height
- Landscape horizontal shortcuts: map/media split by `mapMediaRatio`; vertical shortcuts: narrow icon-only dock (`wrapContentWidth()`), map/media share remaining Row width by ratio
- Horizontal dock compact sizes: `DockHorizontalTapTarget` 48dp, `DockHorizontalIconSize` 40dp — do not reuse `MinTapTarget`/`AppIconSize` for horizontal bar
- `LauncherViewModel.updateMapMediaRatio()` not `setMapMediaRatio()` — JVM signature clash with `mapMediaRatio` property setter
- Media controls in `MediaPlayerPane.kt`: each button in `Row` needs `Modifier.weight(1f)` + `requiredSize(MinTapTarget)` or last button shrinks when pane is narrow
- Now playing: `MediaSessionRepository` + `MixAutoNotificationListenerService`; user must enable Notification access — `MediaSessionManager.getActiveSessions()` requires enabled listener component
- Shared overlay dismiss: `OverlayCloseButton` in `ui/components/` — use for full-screen dialogs (settings, search), not text Close buttons
- `MainActivity.onResume()` calls `MediaSessionRepository.refreshSessions()` after returning from notification-access settings or media apps
- Offline Overture POI build/publish tools live in sibling repo **`mix-auto-overture-maps/tools/`** — not `mix-auto/tools/`; `mix-auto/tools/README.md` is a pointer only
- App catalog: `MapDataViewModel` fetches `countries.json` from `kyuusanq3/mix-auto-overture-maps/releases/latest/download/`; per-country URL is `{RELEASE_BASE}/{asset}` from manifest — no app update needed when publishing new release tags marked Latest
- GitHub release must **attach** `countries.json` + `{iso}_places.db.gz` as release assets; a release with zero assets returns 404 on `/latest/download/` even if the tag exists
- Philippines pack sizes: ~137 MB compressed (`ph_places.db.gz`), ~263 MB installed SQLite; manifest `size_compressed_mb` / `size_db_mb` drives UI labels
- `LocalPlacesRepository.downloadDatabaseFromUrl()` decompresses `.gz`; manual `importDatabaseFromUri()` does NOT — sideload uncompressed `.db` only
- `MapDataOverlay` header copy still says "~50 MB compressed" — per-row sizes from catalog are correct (~137 MB for PH)
- Destination search distance: default **500 km** cap via `MAX_SEARCH_RADIUS_M` in `MapLibreEngineImpl`; filter runs after `mergeAndDeduplicate()` when `limitDistance` is true — local SQLite bbox (±0.5°) unchanged
- Launcher Settings toggle **"Nearby results only (within 500 km)"** (`LauncherPreferences.limitSearchDistance`, default ON) flows DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay → `searchDestination(limitDistance)`; include `limitSearchDistance` in search `LaunchedEffect` keys so toggling re-queries
- Photon returns global results (lat/lon is bias only); public OSRM demo server cannot reliably route intercontinental or 5000+ km trips — distance limit protects search UX, not routing capability
- POI map pins: camera-idle listener (zoom ≥ 13, 1.5 s debounce) loads local Overture bbox first then merges Photon; use `mergePoiPins()` not `mergeAndDeduplicate()` for pin layer — latter re-sorts by distance and evicts categorized local pins
- `PoiIconFactory.kt` generates category teardrop bitmaps (F/G/H/A/$/S/R/•); SymbolLayer uses data-driven `iconImage` from normalized Overture/Photon category
- Vector tiles: `LauncherPreferences.useVectorTiles` (default **true** on first launch) → `CarMapEngine.setMapStyle()`; raster OSM JSON vs OpenFreeMap Liberty `https://tiles.openfreemap.org/styles/liberty`
- App display name **Mix Auto** (`strings.xml`); theme style `Theme.MixAuto` (renamed from `Theme.MyApplication`)
- Launcher icon: `ic_launcher_background.xml` solid `#000000`, `ic_launcher_foreground.xml` cyan pin `#00E5FF` with white center dot
- **Navigation App Mode** default: `MainActivity` intent-filter is LAUNCHER only; `LauncherModeAlias` (HOME+DEFAULT) `android:enabled="false"` in manifest — enable via Settings **Launcher Mode** + `MainActivity.applyLauncherMode()` / `PackageManager.setComponentEnabledSetting(..., DONT_KILL_APP)`
- `LauncherPreferences.isLauncherMode` default false; toggled in `LauncherViewModel.toggleLauncherMode()`; restored in `onCreate()` before UI
- Current release: `versionCode = 6`, `versionName = "0.0.6"`; signed release APK at `mix-auto.apk` (project root, gitignored); upload manually to GitHub release
- Off-route reroute: `routeGeometryPoints` + `checkOffRoute()` in `evaluateStepAdvancement()` — 75 m threshold, **1** consecutive off-route fix (`REROUTE_CONFIRM_COUNT = 1`), 5 s cooldown; `startNavigation(..., isReroute=true)` skips `showRouteThenDive()` and calls `enterNavigationCamera()` directly
- Route line vanishing on raster style: first `drawRoute()` add uses `style.addLayerAbove(routeLayer, "osm")` — do not use plain `addLayer()` or line renders under tiles
- Waze-style puck: `applyDrivingViewportPadding()` — fraction-based pixel padding (`VIEWPORT_PADDING_LEFT_FRACTION=0.3`, `VIEWPORT_PADDING_TOP_FRACTION=0.4` of map view px dimensions) positions puck at ~65% from left and ~70% from top; uses `map.width`/`map.height` so it scales correctly across all screen sizes and densities; called from `activateLocationTracking()` and `applyFreeDriveToMap()`
- Media auto-play on boot: `MediaSessionRepository.maybeAutoPlay()` once per process (`hasAutoPlayed`) when session has metadata but is not `STATE_PLAYING`; call from `attachController()` **and** retry in `onMetadataChanged()` (late metadata on head unit boot) and same-token re-attach branch; requires notification access enabled; **`ensureDefaultPlayerIfNeeded()`** in `MainActivity.refreshMediaSessionsAndBootAudio()` launches `LauncherPreferences.defaultAudioPackage` once per process when no session, then retries `refreshSessions()` at 2s/5s/10s; register `OnActiveSessionsChangedListener` on first successful refresh
- Default audio source: `LauncherPreferences.defaultAudioPackage` (key `default_audio_package`, empty = unset) → `LauncherViewModel.updateDefaultAudioPackage()`; clear on init if `canLaunchApp()` fails; no default + no session → inline `AudioPlayerListContent` in `MediaPlayerPane` ("Choose the default audio source", tap sets default + launches); default set + idle → normal player + boot launch fallback; active session always wins in `selectController()`
- Audio player picker: shared `AudioPlayerListContent` in `AudioPlayerPickerOverlay.kt` — overlay tap launches app only; long-press → confirm dialog → set default; row suffix `(Default)`; overlay bottom hint **Long press to set as default** (`showLongPressHint` false in setup mode)
- Large shortcut icons: `LauncherPreferences.isLargeShortcutIcons` (default **true** on first launch) → Settings **Large Shortcut Icons**; doubles `DockHorizontalTapTarget`/`DockHorizontalIconSize`/`AppIconSize` in `ShortcutDock`
- Synthetic bearing in `MapLibreEngineImpl.enrichLocationWithBearing()`: when `hasBearing()` is false (emulator/mock GPS), compute heading from previous fix via `bearingTo()` if movement > 10 m and speed ≥ 1.4 m/s (or `hasSpeed()` false) — prevents north-up camera and jitter-spin when parked
- Bearing freeze when stopped: `enrichLocationWithBearing()` checks `STOPPED_SPEED_MPS` (1.4 m/s) **before** the `hasBearing()` early-return; applies `lastStableBearing` when stopped so puck does not spin in traffic/parking; update `lastStableBearing` while moving or from synthetic bearing
- Dead-reckoning puck: `startDeadReckoning()` extrapolates position at `DEAD_RECKONING_INTERVAL_MS` (16 ms) between GPS fixes using last speed + bearing; visual-only `forceLocationUpdate()` — does not call `evaluateStepAdvancement()`; cancelled on each real fix, when speed < 1.4 m/s, `startFreeDrive()`, and `onDestroy()`; requires `import kotlinx.coroutines.isActive`
- Route line styling: `ROUTE_WIDTH` 14f with `ROUTE_CASING_LAYER_ID` (18f, `#CC000000`) below cyan line in `drawRoute()` — add casing above `osm`, route above casing; remove both layers in `applyFreeDriveToMap()`
- Android Studio AVD x86_64 GPS (all API levels, Google Play and AOSP images): `adb emu geo fix` returns `OK` but `Number of location reports: 0` — GNSS HAL is broken; workaround is `avd-gps.ps1` at repo root which uses `cmd location providers add-test-provider gps` after `adb root`
- Android 12+ (API 31) `cmd location providers` mock GPS: `LocationManagerService.addTestProvider` calls `noteOp(OP_MOCK_LOCATION, callingUid, "android")` — default mode is `MODE_ERRORED`; `appops set shell android:mock_location allow` does NOT work (wrong package/uid binding); must grant by uid number: `cmd appops set 0 MOCK_LOCATION allow` and `cmd appops set 2000 MOCK_LOCATION allow` (as root) before calling `cmd location providers`
- `avd-gps.ps1`: run once per emulator boot; `.\avd-gps.ps1` for single fix at Gov Center, `.\avd-gps.ps1 -Drive` for 39 road-snapped fixes Gov Center → SM City Bacolod via OSRM, `.\avd-gps.ps1 LAT LNG` for custom fix
- PowerShell URL construction with doubles: always use `InvariantCulture` formatting and concatenate query string separately — PowerShell 7 null-conditional `?.` parses `$varS?query` as null-conditional in double-quoted strings, silently dropping the variable value
- Release signing: keystore at `app/mixauto-release.jks` (alias `mixauto`, RSA 2048, 10 000-day validity); `signingConfigs { create("release") }` in `app/build.gradle.kts`; credentials stored in plaintext (personal sideload only — move to `keystore.properties` before Play Store)
- Release APK workflow: `.\gradlew.bat assembleRelease` → copy `app/build/outputs/apk/release/app-release.apk` to `mix-auto.apk` at repo root (no version suffix); use `/local-apk` skill to run this workflow
- `/local-apk` skill commit message is derived from **local uncommitted changes on dev** (`git diff --stat` + `git diff --stat --cached` + `git log --oneline -10`) — NOT from `main..dev` diff; the `main..dev` range covers the full branch history and produces an overly broad commit message
- `mix-auto.apk` and `app/mixauto-release.jks` should be in `.gitignore`
- TomTom traffic overlay: `LauncherPreferences.showTraffic` + `tomTomApiKey`; `MapLibreEngineImpl.applyTrafficOverlay()` adds `RasterSource` via `TileSet("2.1.0", url)` (not direct URL constructor — `{z}/{x}/{y}` placeholder bug); layer IDs `mix-traffic-source` / `mix-traffic-layer`; Orbis v2 URL `https://api.tomtom.com/maps/orbis/traffic/flow/raster/tile/{z}/{x}/{y}?apiVersion=2&key={KEY}&style=light&tileSize=256` — valid styles **`light`** and **`dark`** only
- TomTom key check: `TomTomTrafficClient.verifyApiKey()` + Map Data panel **Test TomTom API Key** button (`TomTomApiKeySection` in `MapDataOverlay.kt`); `LauncherViewModel.updateTomTomApiKey()` not `setTomTomApiKey()` (JVM signature clash with property setter); Traffic Overlay toggle stays in Launcher Settings
- Google Places POI caching prohibited by Google Maps Platform ToS even when device has Play Services; TomTom Places or Overture offline DB are cache-friendly alternatives
- Recent destinations: `LauncherPreferences.recentDestinations` JSON (max 10, 50 m dedup); `LauncherViewModel.addRecentDestination()`; wired MainActivity → DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay via `onDestinationSelected`
- Saved places: `LauncherPreferences.savedPlaces` JSON (max 50, 50 m dedup); `LauncherViewModel.toggleSavedPlace()` / `isPlaceSaved()`; wired MainActivity → DashboardScreen → CarMapViewContainer → NavigationSearchOverlay via `onToggleSavedPlace`
- Map tap anywhere: `MapLibreEngineImpl.addOnMapClickListener` — POI pin hit uses feature props; empty tap finds nearest `poiCache` entry within `MAP_TAP_NEAREST_POI_MAX_M` (500 m) or creates `SearchResultPlace("Dropped Pin", isDroppedPin=true)` with `formatLatLng` subtitle
- POI details drawer: `PoiDetailDrawer.kt` rendered at **DashboardScreen** root `Box` (full screen, covers media pane) — not inside `CarMapViewContainer`; Navigate calls `onDestinationSelected` + `navigateToCoordinates`; star calls `onToggleSavedPlace`
- Starred map pins: `CarMapEngine.setSavedPlaces()` → `savedPlacesKeys` (lat/lng rounded 5 dp) → GeoJSON `starred` property → `poiCategoryIconExpression()` uses `Expression.switchCase` for gold `poi_icon_starred_*` icons from `PoiIconFactory`
- Empty search overlay: **Recent | Saved | Nearby** `TabRow` when `query.length < 2` — replaces merged badge list; each `SearchResultRow` has star `IconButton`; typed results also show star button
- Map/media split: draggable 3-dot `MapMediaDividerHandle` on pane seam in `DashboardScreen.kt` (not Settings slider); ratio 0.3–0.8 persisted via `LauncherPreferences.mapMediaRatio` / `LauncherViewModel.updateMapMediaRatio()`
- Overlay split lock: when `activePanel == ActivePanel.SEARCH` or `ActivePanel.POI_DETAIL`, use `effectiveMapMediaRatio = OVERLAY_MAP_MEDIA_RATIO` (**0.4f** — 40% map / 60% secondary) for layout weights and hide divider via `showMapMediaDivider`; do NOT call `updateMapMediaRatio(0.4f)` — persisted ratio unchanged so dismiss restores user's prior split; Settings / Map Data / Media unaffected
- Map/media divider drag: never put `mapMediaRatio` in `pointerInput` keys — each ratio update restarts the detector and breaks continuous drag; use `rememberUpdatedState` + `onDragStart` + accumulated `totalDragPx`
- Map/media divider touch target: do not use `MinTapTarget` as layout width/height in Row/Column — use `seamTouchTarget` layout modifier (0 dp seam, 64 dp hit area placed centered overlapping panes); RHD horizontal shortcuts need `invertDrag = true`
- Puck position sliders: `puckHorizontalOffset` / `puckVerticalOffset` (default 0.3/0.4) in `LauncherPreferences` flow through `LauncherViewModel` → `CarMapEngine.setViewportPadding()` → `MapLibreEngineImpl`; after calling `paddingWhileTracking`, always call `forceLocationUpdateForImmediateRender()` so the camera repositions without waiting for the next GPS or dead-reckoning tick
- Puck size slider: `puckScale` (default 1.0) controlled via `LocationComponentOptions.maxZoomIconScale` / `minZoomIconScale` + `locationComponent.applyStyle(updated)` — use `toBuilder()` on `component.locationComponentOptions` to preserve other options; `setPuckScale(scale)` is style-only — do NOT call `forceLocationUpdateForImmediateRender()` for scale (causes camera jolt in `TRACKING_GPS`; unlike viewport padding, scale does not need camera reposition); slider uses `onValueChange = onPuckScaleChange` only — do NOT use `onValueChangeFinished` with captured `puckScale` param (stale closure reverts tap/skip before recomposition)
- `applyDrivingTrackingPadding`: do NOT guard with `if (component.cameraMode == CameraMode.NONE) return` — tracking padding must always be stored so it takes effect when tracking resumes after camera detach; `activateLocationTracking` should call `applyDrivingTrackingPadding` (not `applyDrivingViewportPadding`) so `paddingWhileTracking` is initialized on style load
- `computeDrivingViewportPadding` fallback: when `map.width == 0`, use `displayMetrics.widthPixels` / `heightPixels` with the user's fraction fields — never hardcode dp values in the fallback or the slider positions will be silently ignored before layout
- Settings panel in media pane: `SettingsContent` composable root must be `Surface(color = OledBlack)` — without it, `LocalContentColor` defaults to black and all `Text` composables become invisible against the dark background; `MediaOrSettingsPane` composable conditionally renders either `MediaPlayerPane` or `SettingsContent` to avoid a full-screen dialog
- App update check: `AppUpdateRepository` uses GitHub Releases API (`api.github.com/repos/kyuusanq3/mix-auto/releases/latest`) with `Accept: application/vnd.github+json`; compares `tag_name` to `BuildConfig.VERSION_NAME` via `isNewerVersion()` — do not require a `version.json` release asset; APK download stays at `releases/latest/download/mix-auto.apk`
- Album art gestures in `MediaPlayerPane.kt`: double-tap play/pause; swipe L/R prev/next; swipe up like; long-press opens `AlbumArtModePicker` — disable normal `pointerInput` while `isPickerOpen`; swipe down does nothing (shuffle removed)
- Album art modes in `AlbumArtDisplay.kt`: `PLAIN`, `VINYL` (spinning record), `VISUALIZER` (animated bars); `AlbumArtModeContent()` helper; picker tap or second long-press confirms selection
- Vinyl circular clip: apply `clip(CircleShape)` then `graphicsLayer { rotationZ }` on the Box — do not use `Modifier.rotate` before clip (produces rectangular artifact)
- Album art sizing: `BoxWithConstraints` → `(if (maxWidth < maxHeight) maxWidth else maxHeight) * 0.92f` — do not use `kotlin.math.min` on Dp values
- Media like: `MediaSessionRepository.toggleLike()` via `RATING_HEART` / custom actions; never send dislike/thumb_down (YT Music skips on unlike); `likedTrackCache` keyed by media ID
- Media shuffle (repo only): `MediaSessionRepository.toggleShuffle()` + `readShuffleState()` — YT Music returns `SHUFFLE_MODE_INVALID`; use `ACTION_SET_SHUFFLE_MODE` actions-bit for `supportsShuffle` and `cachedShuffleOn` when toggling if mode stays invalid; third-party shuffle UI removed as unreliable
- Transport controls row order: `[Source app] [Prev] [Play/Pause] [Next] [Like]` — first slot is `SourceAppButton`: **tap** = launch `sourcePackage` when session active, else open `AudioPlayerPickerOverlay` (shows default app icon when default set, cyan `MusicNote` when not); **long-press** always opens picker (required after default+boot — active session tap alone only launches app); Like is 5th button with `active = mediaState.isLiked == true`
- Audio player picker (no active session): `MediaPlayerPane` local `showAudioPicker` state + `Box` overlay — NOT `ActivePanel`; `AudioPlayerUtils.loadAudioPlayerApps()` merges `CATEGORY_APP_MUSIC` activities + `MediaBrowserService` services (dedupe, exclude own package, require launch intent); manifest `<queries>` needs both intents for API 30+ visibility; `AudioPlayerPickerOverlay.kt` uses `carLazyScrollbar` + `launchAppByPackage()` on row tap; long-press row to change default
- Source app icon helpers: `ui/components/AppIconUtils.kt` — `rememberAppIcon()`, `canLaunchApp()`, `launchAppByPackage()`; drawable→bitmap via private `Drawable.toImageBitmap()` (no Accompanist)
- Music dock source badge: `ShortcutDock` accepts `sourcePackage`; `MusicDockItem` overlays 20dp circular app icon at `BottomEnd` when icon loads — no fallback badge if load fails
- Panel toggle system: `ActivePanel` enum in `ShortcutDock.kt` (`MEDIA`, `SETTINGS`, `MAP_DATA`, `APP_DRAWER`, `SEARCH`, `POI_DETAIL`, `HIDDEN`); **radio-style dock indicators** — all four dock items derive `isActive` from `activePanel` only (Music = `ActivePanel.MEDIA`, not `musicPaneEnabled`); `musicPaneEnabled` in `DashboardScreen` is internal only — remembers collapsed media for `dismissToBasePanel()` (`HIDDEN` vs `MEDIA`); Music tap from another panel → `ActivePanel.MEDIA`; tap same panel again → dismiss via `dismissToBasePanel()`; dock icon order via `dockItemOrder()`: vertical = `[App Drawer] [Music] [Map Data] [Launcher]` (drawer top); horizontal LHD = App Drawer left (first); horizontal RHD = App Drawer right (last); active state = cyan icon tint + `DockActiveIndicator` (horizontal: 8×4dp bottom pill; vertical: 4×8dp side pill on outer edge — LHD/`CenterEnd`, RHD/`CenterStart` via `isLeftHandDrive`); Map Data renders inline via `MapDataPanelContent` not root dialog
- Map Data panel (`MapDataPanelContent`) lists catalog countries only — no Import/Sample Philippines fallback rows; install via per-country Download from GitHub `countries.json`
- App Drawer overlay: `AppDrawerOverlay.kt` — `PackageManager.queryIntentActivities(ACTION_MAIN/CATEGORY_LAUNCHER)` sorted by label; search filter; tap launch; long-press dropdown App Info / Uninstall; `DashboardScreen` `SplitScreenAppDrawerSlot` overlays **map+media Box only** — do NOT wrap vertical `ShortcutDock` in a Column with drawer above it (malforms dock: floating icons, black gap); vertical dock stays `wrapContentWidth().fillMaxHeight()` sibling of weighted map/media `Box`
- App Drawer missing Google/system apps (Android 11+): `queryIntentActivities` with flag `0` silently omits apps due to package visibility restrictions — fix requires BOTH (1) `<queries><intent><action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN"/><category android:name="android.intent.category.LAUNCHER"/></intent></queries>` block in `AndroidManifest.xml` AND (2) flag `PackageManager.MATCH_ALL` in `loadLaunchableApps()` in `AppDrawerOverlay.kt`
- Vertical shortcut dock (landscape): icon-only — no "Shortcuts" header or per-item labels; `ElevatedCard` uses `wrapContentWidth()` not full column width; `DashboardScreen` uses `.wrapContentWidth().fillMaxHeight()` not `.weight(DockVerticalWeight)` — map/media fill remaining Row space; landscape weights use `mapMediaRatio` / `(1 - mapMediaRatio)` directly; divider container = row width minus measured `verticalDockWidthPx`
- Vertical dock sizing must match horizontal: `DockHorizontalTapTarget` + `DockHorizontalIconSize` (×2 when **Large Shortcut Icons**) for both orientations — do not use `AppIconSize` / `MinTapTarget` for vertical items or Large Icons looks wrong
- Road-snap puck: `snapLocationToRoute()` in `MapLibreEngineImpl` projects GPS fix onto nearest `routeGeometryPoints` segment when within `SNAP_TO_ROUTE_MAX_M = 40f` metres; `applyAndroidLocation()` uses snapped `displayLocation` for puck/HUD/`lastKnownLocation` but passes raw `locationWithBearing` to `evaluateStepAdvancement()` so off-route detection (75 m threshold) is unaffected; helper `closestPointOnSegment()` returns `ClosestSegmentResult(distM, lat, lng)` — do not use `distanceToSegmentMeters()` alone for snap (it discards the projected coordinates)
- Destination voice search: Eonon hardware voice button dispatches `KEYCODE_VOICE_ASSIST` (fallback `KEYCODE_SEARCH`) — `MainActivity.onKeyDown()` consumes only when `LauncherViewModel.isDestinationSearchOpen`; on Gemini-wired head units the key often never reaches the app — use **dock mic shortcut** instead; in-overlay mic trailing icon in `NavigationSearchOverlay` is secondary; requires `RECORD_AUDIO` + `SpeechRecognizer.isRecognitionAvailable()`; hide dock mic and overlay mic when recognizer unavailable
- Voice search dock shortcut: `ShortcutDock` mic item (`voice_search` key, after Music) → `DashboardScreen.onToggleVoiceSearch()` — closed: `setStartVoiceOnSearchOpen()` + open `ActivePanel.SEARCH`; open (search or POI): close panel (POI via `mapEngine.dismissSelectedPoi()`); do NOT re-trigger listening on second tap; `NavigationSearchContent` `LaunchedEffect(Unit)` calls `consumeStartVoiceOnSearchOpen()` then `tryStartVoiceSearch`; re-open while staying on search uses `triggerVoiceSearch()` only if needed — current UX closes instead; `SpeechRecognizer.createSpeechRecognizer(applicationContext)` + `cancel()` before `startListening()`; do not call `rememberInfiniteTransition` inside `if (isListening)` — always create transition, gate alpha instead
- Destination panel active affordance: `isDestinationPanelOpen = activePanel == SEARCH || POI_DETAIL` — **map search button only** uses inverted active colors (cyan background, `OledBlack` icon); dock mic has **no active styling** (always primary tint, no `DockActiveIndicator`) — action-only shortcut
- Permission onboarding wizard: `ui/onboarding/OnboardingWizard.kt` + `LauncherPreferences.onboardingVersion` (key `onboarding_version`, default 0); `CURRENT_ONBOARDING_VERSION = 1`; on launch if stored version < current, show full-screen wizard over `DashboardScreen` with steps filtered by `sinceVersion > onboardingVersion`; on complete persist `onboardingVersion = CURRENT` and call `requestLocationPermissionIfNeeded()` + `MediaSessionRepository.refreshSessions()`; bump `CURRENT_ONBOARDING_VERSION` and add new steps with higher `sinceVersion` when a future update introduces new permissions — do not re-show completed steps
- `OnboardingWizard` root must be `Surface(color = OledBlack)` not bare `Box(background)` — same `LocalContentColor` black-on-black bug as `SettingsContent`; title/body `Car*Text` invisible without Surface; Button labels still render because Button sets its own content color
- POI pin layer (`SymbolLayer`) must use `style.addLayerAbove(poiLayer, RASTER_BASE_LAYER_ID)` on first add — plain `style.addLayer()` renders the layer below the OSM raster tiles and pins become invisible; fall back to `addLayer()` only when `RASTER_BASE_LAYER_ID` is absent (vector style)
- 3D buildings toggle: `LauncherPreferences.show3dBuildings` (key `show_3d_buildings`, default **false** on first launch) → `LauncherViewModel.toggleShow3dBuildings()` → `CarMapEngine.setShow3dBuildings()` → `MapLibreEngineImpl.apply3dBuildingVisibility(style)` iterates `style.layers` and sets `Property.NONE`/`Property.VISIBLE` on every `FillExtrusionLayer`; called on style load AND on toggle; toggle is disabled (38% alpha) in `SettingsSwitchRow` when vector tiles is off
- `SettingsSwitchRow` in `DashboardScreen.kt` accepts optional `enabled: Boolean = true` — when false, applies `Modifier.alpha(0.38f)` on the Row and passes `enabled = false` to `Switch`; import `androidx.compose.ui.draw.alpha`
- First-launch defaults in `LauncherPreferences.kt` (SharedPreferences fallback when key absent): horizontal shortcuts ON (`isShortcutsHorizontal`), large shortcut icons ON, vector tiles ON, 3D buildings OFF; existing installs keep saved prefs — clear app data to re-test defaults
- Custom pin drop: **long press only** via `addOnMapLongClickListener` in `MapLibreEngineImpl`; short tap uses `handleMapPointSelection()` (saved layer → custom pin layer → POI layer) — no draft on tap
- Custom pin long-press in free drive (`!isNavigating && !isCameraDetached`): `exitFreeDriveToTopViewIfNeeded()` → `animateTopDownCamera()` at drop lat/lng (tilt 0°, `CameraMode.NONE`, `isCameraDetached = true`); skip if user already manually detached camera
- Saved/starred custom pin tap: query `SAVED_PLACES_LAYER_ID` first; `focusOnPoi(..., moveCamera = true)` centers map on pin; `focusOnPoi()` calls `clearCustomPin()` when `isSavedPlace(place)` — gold ★ on saved layer only, no cyan `+` overlay
- Map pin hit test: use `isTapNearPinIcon()` screen-space radius (`MAP_PIN_ICON_HIT_RADIUS_DP = 38f` × density) — do NOT use geographic `findSavedPlaceAt(tapLat, tapLng)` fallback before drafting (50 m blocked new pins near saved pins)
- Custom pin draft blocked during active navigation (`isNavigating`) on long press
- Vector tile POI overlay pins: `queryTilePois()` must use `map.queryRenderedFeatures(screenBounds, *VECTOR_POI_LAYER_IDS)` with Liberty style layer IDs `poi_r1`, `poi_r7`, `poi_r20`, `poi_transit` — do NOT use `VectorSource.querySourceFeatures("poi")` (tile cache misses POIs already painted on screen)
- Top-view mode: `MapUiState.isInTopDownView` set by `animateTopDownCamera()` (flat tilt 0°, bearing 0°); distinct from `isCameraDetached` (manual pan also sets detached without top-down); cleared on `recenterCamera` / `snapCameraToGpsIfNeeded` / nav camera entry
- Top-view UI in `CarMapViewContainer`: when `isCameraDetached && !isInTopDownView && !isNavigating`, show `TooltipBubble` in a `Row` left of the CropFree `IconButton`; top-right button `Column` must use `horizontalAlignment = Alignment.End` (not `CenterHorizontally`) or narrower Search/Recenter buttons center when tooltip Row is widest child
- `TooltipBubble` in `CarMapViewContainer.kt`: `drawBehind` rounded rect + right-pointing tail; inner text `padding(horizontal = 14.dp, vertical = 6.dp)`; tail tip at `size.width` with `padding(end = tailHeight)` only — do NOT use sibling `Spacer`/`Box.offset` for tail-to-button gap (drawn tail ignores flow layout); tail flush against button (no extra gap constant)
- MapLibre compass default top-right overlaps destination search icon — `MapLibreEngineImpl.configureCompassPosition()` sets `uiSettings.setCompassGravity(Gravity.BOTTOM or Gravity.END)` with `COMPASS_MARGIN_DP` (16f) margins on style load
- Pin tap camera: `handleMapPointSelection()` calls `focusOnPoi(..., moveCamera = true)` → `animateTopDownCamera` at `POI_PREVIEW_ZOOM` (15.5); must `clearViewportPaddingForPreview()` via `paddingTo(0,0,0,0)` + zero `paddingWhileTracking` before animating — free-drive puck padding shifts POI off visual center; `handleMapLayoutChange()` re-centers on `selectedPoi` or `refreshTopDownExploreCamera()` when `isInTopDownView`; guard `applyDrivingViewportPadding` / `applyDrivingTrackingPadding` with `if (isInTopDownView) return`
- Launcher Mode home-button fix: `setComponentEnabledSetting` alone does NOT prompt Android to switch default home — must explicitly request home role after enabling alias; `LauncherModeAlias` requires `android:label="@string/app_name"` or it appears blank in pickers
- `promptSetAsDefaultHome()` must use `window.decorView.postDelayed(200ms)` before showing the prompt — PackageManager needs a tick to register the newly enabled alias
- Do NOT fire `Intent(ACTION_MAIN) + CATEGORY_HOME` to prompt the home picker — on API 35 (Pixel/AOSP) this either redirects to the current default launcher or routes back into `singleTask` MainActivity and disrupts MapLibre, causing a crash
- Home role prompt in `MainActivity`: register `homeRoleRequestLauncher = registerForActivityResult(StartActivityForResult())` as a field (not inside a method); on API 29+ check `roleManager.isRoleAvailable(ROLE_HOME) && !isRoleHeld(ROLE_HOME)` then `homeRoleRequestLauncher.launch(createRequestRoleIntent(ROLE_HOME))`; fallback to `startActivity(Intent(Settings.ACTION_HOME_SETTINGS))` wrapped in `try/catch ActivityNotFoundException`
- Call `promptSetAsDefaultHome()` only from the toggle callback (`onToggleLauncherMode`) when `isLauncherMode` becomes true — NOT from `onCreate` restore path, or it opens the settings screen on every boot
- Custom scrollbars: `ui/components/CarScrollbarModifier.kt` — `carScrollbar(ScrollState)` for `verticalScroll` Column; `carLazyScrollbar(LazyListState)` for `LazyColumn`; apply on fixed viewport (`Surface`/`Box`), not the scrolling child; thumb = `ElectricCyan` 4dp, always visible when overflow; M3 `Modifier.scrollbar` unavailable on BOM 2024.06.00 (M3 1.2.1)
- Settings scroll: `SettingsContent` hoists `rememberScrollState()`, `.carScrollbar(scrollState)` on `Surface`, Column uses same state for `verticalScroll`
- Map Data scroll: `CountryCatalogList` wraps scrollable `Column` in `Box(modifier.carScrollbar(scrollState))`; external `modifier` (e.g. `.weight(1f)`) stays on `Box`
- Destination search scroll: `NavigationSearchOverlay` wraps suggestion/saved and typed-result `LazyColumn`s in `Box` with `.carLazyScrollbar(listState)`; shared `rememberLazyListState()` across mutually exclusive branches
- Destination search toggle: map search icon uses `onToggleSearch` + `isDestinationPanelOpen` from `DashboardScreen` — tap opens `ActivePanel.SEARCH`, tap again (or when POI detail open) dismisses search or `dismissSelectedPoi()`; active = inverted cyan bg + black search icon
- Destination search copy: no Point A/B labels — field label is **Destination** only (`NavigationSearchOverlay.kt`)
- Search origin: `CarMapEngine.resolveSearchOrigin()` — GPS from `MapUiState` → `lastKnownLocation` → map camera when zoom ≥ `ROUTING_MIN_ZOOM` (10); do NOT fall back to `(0,0)` in overlay; `searchDestination()` resolves origin internally too
- Offline DB after app update: `LocalPlacesRepository` init auto-discovers largest `files/places/*.db` when `active_iso` pref missing; `hasInstalledDatabase` checks any installed file (not pref-only); open failure retries after deleting `-wal`/`-shm`/`-journal` sidecars
- Nearby search suggestions: `getNearbyPois()` uses `poiCache` first; when empty and offline DB installed, bbox fallback via `getPlacesInBounds()` (`NEARBY_SEARCH_BBOX_DELTA = 0.08°`) — do not require camera-idle pin load before Suggestions tab shows POIs
- Destination search POI preview: `NavigationSearchContent.onPreviewPlace` → `DashboardScreen.onPreviewSearchPlace` sets `ActivePanel.POI_DETAIL` synchronously — do NOT call `onDismiss()` after `focusOnPoi()` (brief MEDIA panel + lazy padding breaks tile load)
- POI preview camera: `schedulePoiPreviewCameraRetry()` + `moveCamera` (not `animateCamera`); `CarMapEngine.onMapHostLayoutChanged()` from `CarMapViewContainer.onSizeChanged` + `LaunchedEffect(activePanel, effectiveMapMediaRatio, selectedPoi)` in `DashboardScreen.kt`
- Map padding: use `CameraUpdateFactory.paddingTo()` via `applyMapPaddingImmediate()` — lazy `setPadding()` leaves viewport mismatched with MapView size (partial blank tiles in top-view); `scheduleTopDownViewportSync()` re-applies zero padding + camera on next frame
- Top-view explore (CropFree): `TOP_DOWN_EXPLORE_ZOOM = 15.0`; `handleMapLayoutChange()` must refresh when `isInTopDownView` even without `selectedPoi` — call `refreshTopDownExploreCamera()`; `clearPoiOverlay()` on `animateTopDownCamera()`; skip mix POI overlay refresh while `isInTopDownView` (native vector labels remain)
